&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Benefits: Medical, Dental, and Vision coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited PTO + 10 Sick Days + 13 Paid Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave (14 weeks Primary / 7 weeks Secondary)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k &amp;amp; Retirement Planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness Perks: Internet, cell phone, gym, and commuter stipends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid Work Model: 3 days in the NYC office, or fully remote for US-based candidates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diverse &amp;amp; multicultural team, working with colleagues from all over the world&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career Growth: The chance to make an impact at a company recognized by Fortune Magazine as one of America’s Top 500

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Account Executive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New York City (Hybrid) | 🏡 Remote (US)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;About Bidease&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bidease is a fast-growing mobile ad tech company specializing in in-app programmatic advertising. Our Demand-Side Platform (DSP) empowers advertisers to efficiently reach their target audience across mobile devices. We work with top brands, agencies, and app developers to drive measurable growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Account Executive, Americas you’ll play a critical role in expanding Bidease’s footprint, building strategic partnerships, and driving new-business revenue growth through self-generated accounts. If you&#39;re passionate about digital advertising, thrive in a fast-paced environment, and excel at consultative sales—this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the sales cycle—from prospecting and pitching to closing and growing strategic accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain strong client relationships with brands and agencies in the mobile ad tech space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate clients on Bidease’s programmatic solutions, helping them solve business challenges and optimize their advertising performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with product, marketing, ad operations and customer success teams to maximize client success and retention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet and exceed revenue targets by structuring and closing high-value deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as an industry expert, staying up to date with trends in mobile advertising, ad tech, and programmatic buying&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate pipeline tracking, forecasts, and sales reporting in CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel to attend industry events, generating new leads and nurturing existing contacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Host sales-led lunches, dinners, happy hours and other forms of entertainment for clients and prospects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;✅ Proven track record of selling media and performance-based mobile in-app advertising solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;✅ A robust and active network of buyer contacts, including UA Managers or those who hold similar roles overseeing mobile performance advertising budgets.&lt;br&gt;✅ Strong understanding of programmatic advertising, DSPs, and in-app advertising.&lt;br&gt;✅ Demonstrated success in closing new business deals with brands and agencies to drive revenue.&lt;br&gt;✅ Excellent negotiation, presentation, and consultative selling skills.&lt;br&gt;✅ Ability to work independently while thriving in a collaborative, fast-paced environment.&lt;br&gt;✅ Analytical mindset with the ability to craft data-driven solutions for clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why Join Bidease?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Bidease, we believe in empowering our people and fostering a dynamic work environment. Our benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Compensation: $240,000 - $320,000 OTE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Benefits: Medical, Dental, and Vision coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited PTO + 10 Sick Days + 10 Paid Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave (14 weeks Primary / 7 weeks Secondary)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k &amp;amp; Retirement Planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness Perks: Internet, cell phone, gym, and commuter stipends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid Work Model: 3 days in the NYC office, or fully remote for US-based candidates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diverse &amp;amp; multicultural team, working with colleagues from all over the world&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career Growth: The chance to make an impact at a company recognized by Fortune Magazine as one of America’s Top 500 Most Innovative Companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and be part of a team that’s shaping the future of mobile advertising! 🚀&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Bidease&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bidease is a fast-growing mobile ad tech company specializing in &lt;strong&gt;in-app programmatic advertising&lt;/strong&gt;. Our DSP empowers advertisers to efficiently reach their target audiences across mobile devices. We work with top brands, agencies, and app developers to drive measurable growth through data-driven performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Senior Marketing Manager, ABM to own how Bidease engages its most important target accounts. You will work from a defined list of enterprise DSP and SSP targets, build the programs that earn their attention and orchestrate the multi-touch plays that move an account from cold, to familiar, to sales-ready. You&#39;ll partner closely with Sales on account prioritization and with Commercial Operations on the systems and data that power the work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end ABM programs for Bidease&#39;s priority DSP and SSP target accounts, including account mapping, multi-touch program execution, and measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build account maps with Sales, identifying decision-makers, buying committees, and entry points within each target organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and run the mix that warms an account: targeted content, thought leadership, events and field touches, webinars, and nurture tracks tailored to the account and persona.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own account-targeted paid programs - LinkedIn first - aimed at named accounts and personas, not broad audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage channel mix and budget against account engagement and influenced pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with AEs on account prioritization, penetration strategy, and the timing of the handoff from warm to active.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own program-level reporting - account engagement, meetings generated, and influenced pipeline, by DSP and SSP segment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the ABM playbook as you run it, bringing rigor and process to a function being built from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–8 years in ABM, demand gen, or field/enterprise marketing with a track record of engaging and converting target accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to run full-cycle ABM — account selection, mapping, multi-touch program execution, and measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on with account-level LinkedIn paid and the modern marketing stack (HubSpot, Salesforce, Clay, or equivalents).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-native: you already use AI tools daily and want to go much further.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in mobile, adtech, martech, or adjacent SaaS — you understand how enterprise mobile advertising buying works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Sales partnership instincts — you work with AEs, not just alongside them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
